<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747194>
    dc:description "Figure 22. Pseudolunulites irregularis (Roemer); NHMUK BZ 8220; Late Oligocene, Bünde-Doberg, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany; (a) upper surface of free-living colony; (b) early astogeny; (c) ancestrula (lower centre) and periancestrular zooids; (d) characteristic arrangement of autozooids and avicularia; (e) avicularium; (f) autozooids and avicularia from late astogeny at edge of colony. Scale bars: a = 1 mm; b = 500 µm; c, d, f = 200 µm; e = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4747194/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

